item.title: Need help putting [PI] online
item.dc:creator: @AddictivePkz AddictivePkz
item.description:
@AddictivePkz wrote:

Did you portforward and get a no-ip?

The last vid troubled me when i was learning … So after u portforward basically right click ur client and make a copy of it . In the copy Rename it Player’s Client or whatever u want… open it up , go to client.java and hold down the control F buttons and search for “server =” make sure u have a space between them… then in the quotations put ur Host that u created in no-ip for example “Rsps.no-ip.org” . Then save , compile … and X out the player client. go to ur desktop and right click the player client and hit “add to players client” and it will make a winrar file and place it on ur desktop. Go to uppit.com and hit upload and upload the file fro ur desktop and give ur friends the link when its done uploading.

Hope i helped.
